Detailed Description

cvmx_gmx::_tx_ifg

GMX_TX_IFG = Packet TX Interframe Gap

Notes: * Programming IFG1 and IFG2.

For 10/100/1000Mbs half-duplex systems that require IEEE 802.3 compatibility, IFG1 must be in the range of 1-8, IFG2 must be in the range of 4-12, and the IFG1+IFG2 sum must be 12.

For 10/100/1000Mbs full-duplex systems that require IEEE 802.3 compatibility, IFG1 must be in the range of 1-11, IFG2 must be in the range of 1-11, and the IFG1+IFG2 sum must be 12.

For XAUI/10Gbs systems that require IEEE 802.3 compatibility, the IFG1+IFG2 sum must be 12. IFG1[1:0] and IFG2[1:0] must be zero.

For all other systems, IFG1 and IFG2 can be any value in the range of 1-15. Allowing for a total possible IFG sum of 2-30.
